// scripts/cv-fixture-config.js
// W-CORE-VERIFICATION CV-FIXTURE shared config -- the SOLE place that defines
// what the isolated test world looks like. Both the apply-runner and the
// baseline-capture import from here.
//
// Every value below is REAL (read from prod DB in the CV-FIXTURE recon probes)
// or REAL-AND-SAFE (RFC-2606 .invalid TLD for test domains/emails -- by spec
// never deliverable). No fabricated FK ids. UUIDs for created entities are
// generated by the DB at insert time and recorded into the manifest.
//
// MULTI-TENANT ISOLATION POSTURE (Rule Zero):
//   - WALLiam (b16e1039-38ed-43d7-bbc5-dd02bb651bc9) NEVER appears here.
//   - aily (e2619717-6401-4159-8d4c-d5f87651c8d6) NEVER appears here.
//   - The build inserts a NEW tenant (primary) + a NEW tenant (secondary)
//     plus all their agents/carves under those new tenant_ids.
//   - Test geo IDs (Markham muni / York area / Berczy + Box Grove communities)
//     are REAL Toronto-area geo verified by the CV-FIXTURE geo probe; WALLiam
//     has NO carve on any of them (WALLiam's 12 carves are all in Whitby muni
//     + 11 Whitby communities). Carving them under a NEW tenant_id cannot
//     collide with WALLiam's apa rows (apa is per-tenant).

